title: "Association Between Ehlers-Danlos Syndrome and Gender Diversity"
description: "There's a repeatedly-observed association between Ehlers-Danlos syndrome and gender diversity"
date: 2026-07-01
categories: [news, intersex]
---



Jones JT, Black WR, Moser CN, Rush ET, Malloy Walton L. "Gender dysphoria in adolescents with Ehlers–Danlos syndrome." SAGE Open Medicine 2022;10:20503121221146074. DOI: 10.1177/20503121221146074. 

In a study of 166 adolescents at a pediatric EDS clinic, 17% reported gender dysphoria, and among those, most (61%) reported their gender identity as transgender, followed by nonbinary (14%).



Tabernacki T, McLachlan L, Loria M, Gupta S, Banik S, Mishra K, McNamara M. "Prevalence of Hypermobile Ehlers-Danlos Syndrome in Transgender and Gender Diverse Individuals: A Retrospective Cohort Study." LGBT Health 2026. DOI: 10.1177/23258292251382250.

Key finding: the prevalence among TGD individuals assigned female at birth was 2.62%, and among those assigned male at birth, 1.00%, compared with 0.16% and 0.04% in cisgender females and males, respectively, with an odds ratio of about 18.